  "id": "39638",
  "attachmentHtml": "\n<p><strong>PC Number: </strong>2020-0656<br></p><p><strong>Date: </strong>2020-09-20</p><hr><p>\n\n</p><div style=\"line-height:200%\">\n<p style=\"text-indent:1.00in;text-align:left;margin-top:0.17in;margin-bottom:0.00in;\">\nHer Excellency the Governor General in Council, on the recommendation of the Minister of Industry, pursuant to&nbsp;subsection 16(1) of the <em>Statistics Act</em>, approves the tables, as&nbsp;set out in the annexed Schedules 1 and 2, setting forth the&nbsp;rates of remuneration or allowances for enumerators and other persons employed under that Act for activities related to&nbsp;the 2021 Census of Population Program.\n</p><p style=\"text-align:left;margin-top:0.17in;margin-bottom:0.00in;\">\n&nbsp;</p>\n<br style=\"page-break-before:always\">\n<p style=\"text-align:left;margin-top:0.17in;margin-bottom:0.00in;\">\n&nbsp;\n</p><p style=\"text-indent:1.00in;text-align:left;margin-top:0.17in;margin-bottom:0.00in;\">\nSur recommandation du ministre de l’Industrie et&nbsp;en vertu du paragraphe 16(1) de la <em>Loi sur la statistique</em>, Son&nbsp;Excellence la Gouverneure générale en conseil approuve les barèmes figurant aux annexes 1 et 2 ci-après, indiquant les&nbsp;tarifs de la rémunération ou des allocations à payer aux recenseurs et autres personnes employés en vertu de cette loi&nbsp;pour les activités liées au programme du Recensement de&nbsp;la&nbsp;population de 2021.\n</p><p style=\"text-indent:1.00in;text-align:left;margin-top:0.17in;margin-bottom:0.00in;\">\n&nbsp;\n</p><p style=\"text-indent:1.00in;text-align:left;margin-top:0.17in;margin-bottom:0.00in;\">\n&nbsp;</p>\n<br style=\"page-break-before:always\">\n</div><p style=\"text-align:center;margin-top:0.17in;margin-bottom:0.00in;\">\n<strong>SCHEDULE</strong>\n</p><p style=\"text-align:center;margin-top:0.17in;margin-bottom:0.00in;\">\n<strong><u>Annex 1</u></strong>\n</p><p style=\"text-align:center;margin-top:0.00in;margin-bottom:0.00in;\">\n<strong>Hourly rates of pay for<br>\nenumerators and other persons employed under the <em>Statistics Act</em></strong>\n</p><p style=\"text-align:center;margin-top:0.00in;margin-bottom:0.00in;\">\n<strong>for activities related to the 2021 Census of Population (non-core public servants)</strong>\n</p><p style=\"text-align:left;margin-top:0.17in;margin-bottom:0.00in;\">\n&nbsp;\n</p><p style=\"text-align:left;margin-top:0.17in;margin-bottom:0.00in;\">\nThe table below lists the hourly rates of pay and remuneration payable to enumerators and other persons employed under the <em>Statistics Act</em> for activities related to the 2021 Census of Population Program.\n</p><p style=\"text-align:left;margin-top:0.17in;margin-bottom:0.00in;\">\n&nbsp;\n</p>\n<table width=\"635\" cellspacing=\"1\"><tbody><tr valign=\"top\"><td width=\"243\" style=\"border-left-width:2pt;border-left-style:solid;border-top-width:1pt;border-top-style:solid;border-right-width:1pt;border-right-style:solid;border-bottom-width:1pt;border-bottom-style:solid;\"><p style=\"text-align:left;margin-top:0.17in;margin-bottom:0.00in;\">\n<strong>Description</strong></p>\n</td><td colspan=\"6\" width=\"65\" style=\"border-top-width:2pt;border-top-style:solid;border-right-width:2pt;border-right-style:solid;\"><p style=\"text-align:center;margin-top:0.17in;margin-bottom:0.00in;\">\n<strong>Hourly rates</strong></p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr valign=\"top\">\n<td width=\"243\" style=\"border-left-width:2pt;border-left-style:solid;border-top-width:1pt;border-top-style:solid;border-right-width:1pt;border-right-style:solid;\"><p style=\"text-align:left;margin-top:0.00in;margin-bottom:0.00in;\">\n<strong>Non-supervisory employees:</strong> Enumerators, Collection Support Unit operators, crew leader assistants, field operations supervisor assistants, Census Help Line and Data Operations Centre operators</p>\n</td>\n<td width=\"61\" style=\"border-top-width:1pt;border-top-style:solid;border-right-width:1pt;border-right-style:solid;border-bottom-width:1pt;border-bottom-style:solid;\"><p style=\"text-align:center;margin-top:0.00in;margin-bottom:0.00in;\">\n1*</p>\n</td>\n<td width=\"60\" style=\"border-top-width:1pt;border-top-style:solid;border-right-width:2pt;border-right-style:solid;border-bottom-width:1pt;border-bottom-style:solid;\"><p style=\"text-align:center;margin-top:0.00in;margin-bottom:0.00in;\">\n2*</p>\n</td>\n<td width=\"60\" style=\"border-top-width:1pt;border-top-style:solid;border-right-width:2pt;border-right-style:solid;border-bottom-width:1pt;border-bottom-style:solid;\"><p style=\"text-align:center;margin-top:0.00in;margin-bottom:0.00in;\">\n3*</p>\n</td>\n<td width=\"66\" style=\"border-top-width:1pt;border-top-style:solid;border-right-width:2pt;border-right-style:solid;border-bottom-width:1pt;border-bottom-style:solid;\"><p style=\"text-align:center;margin-top:0.00in;margin-bottom:0.00in;\">\n4*</p>\n</td>\n<td width=\"66\" style=\"border-top-width:1pt;border-top-style:solid;border-right-width:2pt;border-right-style:solid;border-bottom-width:1pt;border-bottom-style:solid;\"><p style=\"text-align:center;margin-top:0.00in;margin-bottom:0.00in;\">\n5*</p>\n</td>\n<td width=\"78\" style=\"border-top-width:1pt;border-top-style:solid;border-right-width:2pt;border-right-style:solid;border-bottom-width:1pt;border-bottom-style:solid;\"><p style=\"text-align:center;margin-top:0.00in;margin-bottom:0.00in;\">\nNorthern Rate**</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr valign=\"top\">\n<td width=\"243\" style=\"border-left-width:2pt;border-left-style:solid;border-right-width:1pt;border-right-style:solid;\">&nbsp;</td>\n<td width=\"61\" style=\"border-top-width:1pt;border-top-style:solid;border-right-width:1pt;border-right-style:solid;border-bottom-width:1pt;border-bottom-style:solid;\"><p style=\"text-align:center;margin-top:0.17in;margin-bottom:0.00in;\">\n$17.83</p>\n</td>\n<td width=\"60\" style=\"border-top-width:1pt;border-top-style:solid;border-right-width:2pt;border-right-style:solid;border-bottom-width:1pt;border-bottom-style:solid;\"><p style=\"text-align:center;margin-top:0.17in;margin-bottom:0.00in;\">\n$18.82</p>\n</td>\n<td width=\"60\" style=\"border-top-width:1pt;border-top-style:solid;border-right-width:2pt;border-right-style:solid;border-bottom-width:1pt;border-bottom-style:solid;\"><p style=\"text-align:center;margin-top:0.17in;margin-bottom:0.00in;\">\n$19.79</p>\n</td>\n<td width=\"66\" style=\"border-top-width:1pt;border-top-style:solid;border-right-width:2pt;border-right-style:solid;border-bottom-width:1pt;border-bottom-style:solid;\"><p style=\"text-align:center;margin-top:0.17in;margin-bottom:0.00in;\">\n$20.77</p>\n</td>\n<td width=\"66\" style=\"border-top-width:1pt;border-top-style:solid;border-right-width:2pt;border-right-style:solid;border-bottom-width:1pt;border-bottom-style:solid;\"><p style=\"text-align:center;margin-top:0.17in;margin-bottom:0.00in;\">\n21.78</p>\n</td>\n<td width=\"78\" style=\"border-top-width:1pt;border-top-style:solid;border-right-width:2pt;border-right-style:solid;border-bottom-width:1pt;border-bottom-style:solid;\"><p style=\"text-align:center;margin-top:0.17in;margin-bottom:0.00in;\">\n$29.25</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr valign=\"top\">\n<td width=\"243\" style=\"border-left-width:2pt;border-left-style:solid;border-right-width:1pt;border-right-style:solid;border-bottom-width:2pt;border-bottom-style:solid;\"><p style=\"text-align:left;margin-top:0.17in;margin-bottom:0.00in;\">\n<strong>Supervisory employees:</strong> Crew leaders </p>\n</td>\n<td width=\"61\" style=\"border-right-width:1pt;border-right-style:solid;border-bottom-width:2pt;border-bottom-style:solid;\"><p style=\"text-align:center;margin-top:0.17in;margin-bottom:0.00in;\">\n$21.77</p>\n</td>\n<td width=\"60\" style=\"border-right-width:2pt;border-right-style:solid;border-bottom-width:2pt;border-bottom-style:solid;\"><p style=\"text-align:center;margin-top:0.17in;margin-bottom:0.00in;\">\n$22.94</p>\n</td>\n<td width=\"60\" style=\"border-right-width:2pt;border-right-style:solid;border-bottom-width:2pt;border-bottom-style:solid;\"><p style=\"text-align:center;margin-top:0.17in;margin-bottom:0.00in;\">\n$24.14</p>\n</td>\n<td width=\"66\" style=\"border-right-width:2pt;border-right-style:solid;border-bottom-width:2pt;border-bottom-style:solid;\"><p style=\"text-align:center;margin-top:0.17in;margin-bottom:0.00in;\">\n$25.31</p>\n</td>\n<td width=\"66\" style=\"border-right-width:2pt;border-right-style:solid;border-bottom-width:2pt;border-bottom-style:solid;\"><p style=\"text-align:center;margin-top:0.17in;margin-bottom:0.00in;\">\n$26.50</p>\n</td>\n<td width=\"78\" style=\"border-right-width:2pt;border-right-style:solid;border-bottom-width:2pt;border-bottom-style:solid;\"><p style=\"text-align:center;margin-top:0.17in;margin-bottom:0.00in;\">\n$31.25\n</p>\n&nbsp;</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;margin-top:0.17in;margin-bottom:0.11in;\">\n* These hourly rates reflect those of the Statistical Survey Operations (SSO) in effect under the current collective agreements. \n</p><p style=\"text-align:left;margin-top:0.17in;margin-bottom:0.11in;\">\n** The Northern rates are based on averages of the existing competitive pay rates used in the Northwest Territories and Yukon Territory, to pay statistical workers in the North.\n</p><p style=\"text-align:left;margin-top:0.17in;margin-bottom:0.00in;\">\n<em>Statistics Act</em> census employees who are approved to work in excess of 520 hours during a calendar quarter, as defined below, are entitled to compensation at time and one-half for all overtime hours worked for the remainder of that quarter, beginning on the 521st hour. The overtime rate is applied to all hours worked once the maximum quarterly hours are reached.\n</p><p style=\"text-align:left;margin-top:0.17in;margin-bottom:0.00in;\">\nQuarterly hours shall be defined as follows for all <em>Statistics Act</em> census employees, irrespective of their date of hiring:\n</p><p style=\"margin-left:0.50in;text-align:left;margin-top:0.00in;margin-bottom:0.00in;\">\n·\t&nbsp;January 1 to March 31\n</p><p style=\"margin-left:0.50in;text-align:left;margin-top:0.00in;margin-bottom:0.00in;\">\n·\t&nbsp;April 1 to June 30\n</p><p style=\"margin-left:0.50in;text-align:left;margin-top:0.00in;margin-bottom:0.00in;\">\n·\t&nbsp;July 1 to September 30\n</p><p style=\"margin-left:0.50in;text-align:left;margin-top:0.00in;margin-bottom:0.00in;\">\n·\t&nbsp;October 1 to December 31.\n</p><p style=\"text-indent:1.00in;text-align:left;margin-top:0.17in;margin-bottom:0.00in;\">\n&nbsp;\n</p><p style=\"text-indent:1.00in;text-align:left;margin-top:0.17in;margin-bottom:0.00in;\">\n&nbsp;</p>\n<br style=\"page-break-before:always\">\n<p style=\"text-align:center;margin-top:0.17in;margin-bottom:0.00in;\">\n<strong>ANNEXE</strong>\n</p><p style=\"text-align:center;margin-top:0.17in;margin-bottom:0.00in;\">\n<strong><u>Annexe 1</u></strong>\n</p><p style=\"text-align:center;margin-top:0.00in;margin-bottom:0.00in;\">\n<strong>Taux de rémunération horaires pour<br>\nles recenseurs et autres personnes employés en vertu de la <em>Loi sur la statistique</em></strong>\n</p><p style=\"text-align:center;margin-top:0.00in;margin-bottom:0.00in;\">\n<strong>pour les activités liées au Recensement de la population de 2021 (non-fonctionnaires)</strong>\n</p><p style=\"text-align:left;margin-top:0.17in;margin-bottom:0.00in;\">\n&nbsp;\n</p><p style=\"text-align:left;margin-top:0.17in;margin-bottom:0.00in;\">\nLe tableau ci-dessous énumère les taux de rémunération horaires et la rémunération payable aux recenseurs et autres personnes employés en vertu de la <em>Loi sur la statistique</em> pour les activités liées au Recensement de la population de 2021.\n</p><p style=\"text-align:left;margin-top:0.17in;margin-bottom:0.00in;\">\n&nbsp;\n</p>\n<table width=\"635\" cellspacing=\"1\"><tbody><tr valign=\"top\"><td width=\"243\" style=\"border-left-width:2pt;border-left-style:solid;border-top-width:1pt;border-top-style:solid;border-right-width:1pt;border-right-style:solid;border-bottom-width:1pt;border-bottom-style:solid;\"><p style=\"text-align:left;margin-top:0.17in;margin-bottom:0.00in;\">\n<strong>Description</strong></p>\n</td><td colspan=\"6\" width=\"65\" style=\"border-top-width:2pt;border-top-style:solid;border-right-width:2pt;border-right-style:solid;\"><p style=\"text-align:center;margin-top:0.17in;margin-bottom:0.00in;\">\n<strong>Taux horaires</strong></p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr valign=\"top\">\n<td width=\"243\" style=\"border-left-width:2pt;border-left-style:solid;border-top-width:1pt;border-top-style:solid;border-right-width:1pt;border-right-style:solid;\"><p style=\"text-align:left;margin-top:0.00in;margin-bottom:0.00in;\">\n<strong>Employés sans fonctions de supervision&nbsp;:</strong> recenseurs, téléphonistes de la Sous-section du soutien à la collecte, adjoints au chef d’équipe, adjoints au chargé des opérations sur le terrain, téléphonistes de l’Assistance téléphonique du recensement et du Centre des opérations des données</p>\n</td>\n<td width=\"61\" style=\"border-top-width:1pt;border-top-style:solid;border-right-width:1pt;border-right-style:solid;border-bottom-width:1pt;border-bottom-style:solid;\"><p style=\"text-align:center;margin-top:0.00in;margin-bottom:0.00in;\">\n1*</p>\n</td>\n<td width=\"60\" style=\"border-top-width:1pt;border-top-style:solid;border-right-width:2pt;border-right-style:solid;border-bottom-width:1pt;border-bottom-style:solid;\"><p style=\"text-align:center;margin-top:0.00in;margin-bottom:0.00in;\">\n2*</p>\n</td>\n<td width=\"60\" style=\"border-top-width:1pt;border-top-style:solid;border-right-width:2pt;border-right-style:solid;border-bottom-width:1pt;border-bottom-style:solid;\"><p style=\"text-align:center;margin-top:0.00in;margin-bottom:0.00in;\">\n3*</p>\n</td>\n<td width=\"66\" style=\"border-top-width:1pt;border-top-style:solid;border-right-width:2pt;border-right-style:solid;border-bottom-width:1pt;border-bottom-style:solid;\"><p style=\"text-align:center;margin-top:0.00in;margin-bottom:0.00in;\">\n4*</p>\n</td>\n<td width=\"66\" style=\"border-top-width:1pt;border-top-style:solid;border-right-width:2pt;border-right-style:solid;border-bottom-width:1pt;border-bottom-style:solid;\"><p style=\"text-align:center;margin-top:0.00in;margin-bottom:0.00in;\">\n5*</p>\n</td>\n<td width=\"78\" style=\"border-top-width:1pt;border-top-style:solid;border-right-width:2pt;border-right-style:solid;border-bottom-width:1pt;border-bottom-style:solid;\"><p style=\"text-align:center;margin-top:0.00in;margin-bottom:0.00in;\">\nTaux pour le Nord**</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr valign=\"top\">\n<td width=\"243\" style=\"border-left-width:2pt;border-left-style:solid;border-right-width:1pt;border-right-style:solid;\">&nbsp;</td>\n<td width=\"61\" style=\"border-top-width:1pt;border-top-style:solid;border-right-width:1pt;border-right-style:solid;border-bottom-width:1pt;border-bottom-style:solid;\"><p style=\"text-align:center;margin-top:0.17in;margin-bottom:0.00in;\">\n17,83&nbsp;$</p>\n</td>\n<td width=\"60\" style=\"border-top-width:1pt;border-top-style:solid;border-right-width:2pt;border-right-style:solid;border-bottom-width:1pt;border-bottom-style:solid;\"><p style=\"text-align:center;margin-top:0.17in;margin-bottom:0.00in;\">\n18,82&nbsp;$</p>\n</td>\n<td width=\"60\" style=\"border-top-width:1pt;border-top-style:solid;border-right-width:2pt;border-right-style:solid;border-bottom-width:1pt;border-bottom-style:solid;\"><p style=\"text-align:center;margin-top:0.17in;margin-bottom:0.00in;\">\n19,79 $</p>\n</td>\n<td width=\"66\" style=\"border-top-width:1pt;border-top-style:solid;border-right-width:2pt;border-right-style:solid;border-bottom-width:1pt;border-bottom-style:solid;\"><p style=\"text-align:center;margin-top:0.17in;margin-bottom:0.00in;\">\n20,77&nbsp;$</p>\n</td>\n<td width=\"66\" style=\"border-top-width:1pt;border-top-style:solid;border-right-width:2pt;border-right-style:solid;border-bottom-width:1pt;border-bottom-style:solid;\"><p style=\"text-align:center;margin-top:0.17in;margin-bottom:0.00in;\">\n21,78&nbsp;$</p>\n</td>\n<td width=\"78\" style=\"border-top-width:1pt;border-top-style:solid;border-right-width:2pt;border-right-style:solid;border-bottom-width:1pt;border-bottom-style:solid;\"><p style=\"text-align:center;margin-top:0.17in;margin-bottom:0.00in;\">\n29,25&nbsp;$</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr valign=\"top\">\n<td width=\"243\" style=\"border-left-width:2pt;border-left-style:solid;border-right-width:1pt;border-right-style:solid;border-bottom-width:2pt;border-bottom-style:solid;\"><p style=\"text-align:left;margin-top:0.17in;margin-bottom:0.00in;\">\n<strong>Superviseurs&nbsp;:</strong> chef d’équipe </p>\n</td>\n<td width=\"61\" style=\"border-right-width:1pt;border-right-style:solid;border-bottom-width:2pt;border-bottom-style:solid;\"><p style=\"text-align:center;margin-top:0.17in;margin-bottom:0.00in;\">\n21,77&nbsp;$</p>\n</td>\n<td width=\"60\" style=\"border-right-width:2pt;border-right-style:solid;border-bottom-width:2pt;border-bottom-style:solid;\"><p style=\"text-align:center;margin-top:0.17in;margin-bottom:0.00in;\">\n22,94 $</p>\n</td>\n<td width=\"60\" style=\"border-right-width:2pt;border-right-style:solid;border-bottom-width:2pt;border-bottom-style:solid;\"><p style=\"text-align:center;margin-top:0.17in;margin-bottom:0.00in;\">\n24,14&nbsp;$</p>\n</td>\n<td width=\"66\" style=\"border-right-width:2pt;border-right-style:solid;border-bottom-width:2pt;border-bottom-style:solid;\"><p style=\"text-align:center;margin-top:0.17in;margin-bottom:0.00in;\">\n25,31&nbsp;$</p>\n</td>\n<td width=\"66\" style=\"border-right-width:2pt;border-right-style:solid;border-bottom-width:2pt;border-bottom-style:solid;\"><p style=\"text-align:center;margin-top:0.17in;margin-bottom:0.00in;\">\n26,50&nbsp;$</p>\n</td>\n<td width=\"78\" style=\"border-right-width:2pt;border-right-style:solid;border-bottom-width:2pt;border-bottom-style:solid;\"><p style=\"text-align:center;margin-top:0.17in;margin-bottom:0.00in;\">\n31,25 $\n</p>\n&nbsp;</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;margin-top:0.17in;margin-bottom:0.11in;\">\n*Les taux horaires correspondent aux taux des Opérations des enquêtes statistiques (OES) qui sont en vigueur selon les conventions collectives actuelles. \n</p><p style=\"text-align:left;margin-top:0.17in;margin-bottom:0.11in;\">\n**Les taux appliqués dans le Nord sont basés sur les moyennes des taux de rémunération concurrentiels en vigueur dans les Territoires du Nord-Ouest et au Yukon pour payer les employés dans le domaine des statistiques dans le Nord.\n</p><p style=\"text-align:left;margin-top:0.17in;margin-bottom:0.00in;\">\nLes employés du recensement recrutés en vertu de la <em>Loi sur la statistique</em> qui sont autorisés à travailler plus de 520&nbsp;heures au cours d’un trimestre civil, comme il est défini ci-dessous, ont droit à une rémunération au taux majoré de moitié pour toutes les heures supplémentaires travaillées pendant le reste du trimestre, à compter de la 521<sup>e</sup>&nbsp;heure. Le taux des heures supplémentaires s’applique à toutes les heures travaillées au-delà du nombre maximal d’heures par trimestre.\n</p><p style=\"text-align:left;margin-top:0.17in;margin-bottom:0.00in;\">\nLe nombre d’heures par trimestre sera établi selon les trimestres suivants dans le cas de tous les employés du recensement recrutés en vertu de la <em>Loi sur la statistique</em>, peu importe leur date d’embauche&nbsp;:\n</p><p style=\"margin-left:0.50in;text-align:left;margin-top:0.00in;margin-bottom:0.00in;\">\n·\t&nbsp;1<sup>er&nbsp;</sup>janvier au 31&nbsp;mars;\n</p><p style=\"margin-left:0.50in;text-align:left;margin-top:0.00in;margin-bottom:0.00in;\">\n·\t&nbsp;1<sup>er</sup>&nbsp;avril au 30&nbsp;juin;\n</p><p style=\"margin-left:0.50in;text-align:left;margin-top:0.00in;margin-bottom:0.00in;\">\n·\t&nbsp;1<sup>er</sup>&nbsp;juillet au 30&nbsp;septembre;\n</p><p style=\"margin-left:0.50in;text-align:left;margin-top:0.00in;margin-bottom:0.00in;\">\n·\t&nbsp;1<sup>er&nbsp;</sup>octobre au 31&nbsp;décembre.\n</p><p style=\"margin-left:0.50in;text-align:left;margin-top:0.00in;margin-bottom:0.00in;\">\n&nbsp;\n</p><p style=\"text-indent:1.00in;text-align:left;margin-top:0.17in;margin-bottom:0.00in;\">\n&nbsp;</p>\n<br style=\"page-break-before:always\">\n<p style=\"text-align:center;margin-top:0.17in;margin-bottom:0.00in;\">\n<strong>SCHEDULE</strong>\n</p><p style=\"text-align:center;margin-top:0.17in;margin-bottom:0.00in;\">\n<strong><u>Annex 2</u></strong>\n</p><p style=\"margin-right:0.00in;text-align:center;margin-top:0.17in;margin-bottom:0.00in;\">\n&nbsp;<strong> Allowances and travel reimbursement for<br>\nenumerators and other persons employed under the <em>Statistics Act</em> for activities related to the 2021</strong>&nbsp;<strong>Census of Population (non-core public servants)</strong>\n</p><p style=\"margin-right:0.00in;text-align:left;margin-top:0.17in;margin-bottom:0.00in;\">\n&nbsp;\n</p><p style=\"margin-right:0.00in;text-align:left;margin-top:0.17in;margin-bottom:0.00in;\">\n<strong><u>Allowances:</u></strong>\n</p><p style=\"text-align:left;margin-top:0.17in;margin-bottom:0.00in;\">\n<strong>Equipment allowance</strong>— Supervisory employees (crew leaders<strong>), </strong>enumerators, crew leader assistants and field operations supervisor assistants employed under the <em>Statistics Act</em> for activities related to the 2021 Census of Population are required to access and provide information online. This allowance will compensate these census collection staff for the use of their personal computer, printer and printer supplies. Separate rates will apply for supervisory and non-supervisory staff.\n</p><p style=\"text-align:left;margin-top:0.17in;margin-bottom:0.00in;\">\nEquipment allowance (non-supervisory): $0.44/day\n</p><p style=\"text-align:left;margin-top:0.17in;margin-bottom:0.00in;\">\nEquipment allowance (supervisory): $2.19/day\n</p><p style=\"text-align:left;margin-top:0.17in;margin-bottom:0.00in;\">\n&nbsp;\n</p><p style=\"text-align:left;margin-top:0.17in;margin-bottom:0.00in;\">\n<strong>Storage allowance—</strong>Supervisory employees (crew leaders<strong>) </strong>will<strong>&nbsp;</strong>be required to store large quantities of supplies and forms in their homes. This allowance will compensate them for this purpose.\n</p><p style=\"text-align:left;margin-top:0.17in;margin-bottom:0.00in;\">\nStorage space allowance (supervisory employees only): $4.93/day\n</p><p style=\"margin-left:0.13in;margin-right:0.29in;text-align:left;margin-top:0.17in;margin-bottom:0.00in;color:#1F497D;\">\n&nbsp;\n</p><p style=\"margin-left:0.13in;margin-right:0.29in;text-align:left;margin-top:0.17in;margin-bottom:0.00in;color:#1F497D;\">\n&nbsp;\n</p><p style=\"margin-right:0.29in;text-align:left;margin-top:0.17in;margin-bottom:0.00in;\">\n<u><strong>Travel reimbursement:</strong></u>\n</p><p style=\"text-align:left;margin-top:0.17in;margin-bottom:0.00in;\">\nReimbursement of authorized travel expenses for enumerators and other persons employed under the <em>Statistics Act</em> for the 2021 Census of Population will be in accordance with the Treasury Board Directive on Travel, Hospitality, Conference and Event Expenditures and as per the Government-wide Chart of Accounts. All expenses for travel will be paid according to the contract agreements for enumerators and other census collection staff, as they are considered non-public servants. \n</p><p style=\"margin-left:0.50in;text-indent:-0.25in;text-align:left;margin-top:0.17in;margin-bottom:0.00in;\">\n&nbsp;\n</p><p style=\"text-indent:1.00in;text-align:left;margin-top:0.17in;margin-bottom:0.00in;\">\n&nbsp;</p>\n<br style=\"page-break-before:always\">\n<p style=\"text-align:center;margin-top:0.17in;margin-bottom:0.00in;\">\n<strong>ANNEXE</strong>\n</p><p style=\"text-align:center;margin-top:0.17in;margin-bottom:0.00in;\">\n<strong><u>Annexe 2</u></strong>\n</p><p style=\"margin-right:0.00in;text-align:center;margin-top:0.17in;margin-bottom:0.00in;\">\n&nbsp;<strong> Allocations et remboursement des frais de déplacement pour<br>\nles recenseurs et autres personnes employés en vertu de la <em>Loi sur la statistique</em> pour les activités liées au Recensement de la population de 2021 (non-fonctionnaires)</strong>\n</p><p style=\"margin-right:0.00in;text-align:left;margin-top:0.17in;margin-bottom:0.00in;\">\n&nbsp;\n</p><p style=\"margin-right:0.00in;text-align:left;margin-top:0.17in;margin-bottom:0.00in;\">\n<strong><u>Allocations :</u></strong>\n</p><p style=\"text-align:left;margin-top:0.17in;margin-bottom:0.00in;\">\n<strong>Allocation pour le matériel </strong>— Les superviseurs (chefs d’équipe<strong>), </strong>recenseurs, adjoints au chef d’équipe et adjoints au chargé des opérations sur le terrain employés en vertu de la <em>Loi sur la statistique</em> pour les activités liées au Recensement de la population de 2021 doivent avoir accès à de l’information en ligne et être en mesure d’en fournir. L’allocation dédommagera les membres du personnel de la collecte du recensement pour l’utilisation de leur ordinateur personnel, de leur imprimante et de leurs fournitures d’imprimante. Des taux distincts s’appliqueront au personnel avec fonctions de supervision et au personnel sans fonctions de supervision.\n</p><p style=\"text-align:left;margin-top:0.17in;margin-bottom:0.00in;\">\nAllocation pour le matériel (personnel sans fonctions de supervision)&nbsp;: 0,44&nbsp;$ par jour\n</p><p style=\"text-align:left;margin-top:0.17in;margin-bottom:0.00in;\">\nAllocation pour le matériel (personnel avec fonctions de supervision)&nbsp;: 2,19&nbsp;$ par jour\n</p><p style=\"text-align:left;margin-top:0.17in;margin-bottom:0.00in;\">\n&nbsp;\n</p><p style=\"text-align:left;margin-top:0.17in;margin-bottom:0.00in;\">\n<strong>Allocation pour l’entreposage — </strong>Le personnel avec fonctions de supervision (chefs d’équipe<strong>) </strong>devra entreposer une grande quantité de fournitures et de formulaires à leur domicile. Cette allocation les dédommagera à cette fin.\n</p><p style=\"text-align:left;margin-top:0.17in;margin-bottom:0.00in;\">\nAllocation pour l’entreposage (personnel avec fonctions de supervision seulement)&nbsp;: 4,93&nbsp;$&nbsp;par jour \n</p><p style=\"margin-left:0.13in;margin-right:0.29in;text-align:left;margin-top:0.17in;margin-bottom:0.00in;color:#1F497D;\">\n&nbsp;\n</p><p style=\"margin-left:0.13in;margin-right:0.29in;text-align:left;margin-top:0.17in;margin-bottom:0.00in;color:#1F497D;\">\n&nbsp;\n</p><p style=\"margin-right:0.29in;text-align:left;margin-top:0.17in;margin-bottom:0.00in;\">\n<u><strong>Remboursement des frais de déplacement :</strong></u>\n</p><p style=\"text-align:left;margin-top:0.17in;margin-bottom:0.00in;\">\nLe remboursement des frais autorisés de déplacement des recenseurs et autres personnes employés en vertu de la <em>Loi sur la statistique</em> pour les activités liées au Recensement de la population de 2021 se fera conformément à la Directive sur les dépenses de voyages, d’accueil, de conférences et d’événements du Conseil du Trésor et au Plan comptable à l’échelle de l’administration fédérale. Toutes les dépenses de déplacement seront remboursées en fonction des termes du contrat pour les recenseurs et autres membres du personnel de la collecte du recensement puisqu’ils sont considérés comme non-fonctionnaires. \n</p><p style=\"text-indent:1.00in;text-align:left;margin-top:0.17in;margin-bottom:0.00in;\">\n&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p></p><form method=\"post\" action=\"index.php\"><input type=\"submit\" value=\"Back to Form\" class=\"btn btn-primary\" name=\"return\"></form>\t\t\n        <!-- end main content -->\n        <div id=\"def-preFooter\">\n       \t\t<!-- Write closure fall-back static file -->\n             <!--Response.Write readFile(\"StaticFallbackFiles/gcweb/preFooter-\" & $lang & \".html\") -->\n        </div>\n\t\t<!-- Write closure 